1. Introduction to HTML

HTML- is a mark up language
->HMTL is syntax is used to mark up a document.

1.1 HTML-> to write html, we pick from set of standards elements that all browsers recognized.

->Common elements
1. <p>  - Paragraphs elements
2. <img>-embed elements
3. <form> element - represents a form
4. <h1> element- represents the main header on page.

1.2 HTML Tags
->we create elements by writing tags.
->Most(but not all ) elements consist of an opening and closing tag.

<p>it is paragraph</p>

<p>  ->Opening tag
</p> ->closing tag
<h1>HTML tags</h1>

=>Tags
1. Bold tag
hi my name is <b>Ashish</b>. I am full stack developer.

->check MDN
->Element refernce

2. Paragraph tag

->Paragraph take stand alone place.
->it is block level elements.

<p>
    Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet consectetur adipisicing elit. Aperiam est officia eius veritatis amet recusandae.
    Consequuntur odit necessitatibus eveniet! Aliquid laudantium quas facere obcaecati sit molestias quae, enim
    cupiditate esse iste. Voluptatibus earum recusandae iusto necessitatibus at, natus ipsa repellendus a nostrum. Iusto
    earum culpa sit dolores nulla in itaque.
</p>

3. Heading tag
->better to have one h1 tag on page.
->we should never have h3 without h1 and h2.
->we should never have h6 without h5, h4, h3, h2 and h1.
<h1>h1 heading tag</h1>
->we can use other tags for sub headings.
h2, h3, h4, h5 and h6.

<h2>Sub Heading 1</h2>
<p>Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet consectetur, adipisicing elit. Libero aliquam repellendus nobis quam ut omnis temporibus
    placeat perferendis deleniti nihil?</p>

<h3>Sub Heading 2</h3>
<p>Lorem ipsum, dolor sit amet consectetur adipisicing elit. Iure sed eius nam est dolorum optio, amet sapiente beatae
    rem sit.</p>


4. Dummy text
->use lorem(no. of words)
eg: Lorem20
<p>Lorem ipsum dolor, sit amet consectetur adipisicing elit. Assumenda, numquam.</p>

